        <h2 xmlns="">Environmental Health &amp; Safety</h2> 
        <p></p> 
        <p><img class="right border6" src="images/news/captions/2014-lifting-safety-300.jpg" alt="April safety tip:lifting safely"></p>     
        <h2>Safety tip: slips, trips and falls</h2> 
        <p>Slips, trips and falls are the most frequent accidents leading to personal injury. They can result in head injuries, back injuries, broken bones, sprained muscles, or cuts and lacerations. <br><br></p> 
        <p><a href="http://www.greenriver.edu/about-us/campus-news/news/featured/2014-march-safety-tip.htm" title="Safety Tip: slips, trips and falls">Read article in Campus News</a></p> 
        <p></p> 
        <p>__________________________________________________________</p> 
        <h2>Safety tip: lifting safely</h2> 
        <p>Proper lifting technique and appropriate planning is critical to back safety and preventing lifting injuries.<br><br></p> 
        <p><a href="http://www.greenriver.edu/about-us/news/campus-news/featured/2014-april-safety-tip.htm" title="Safety Tip: Lifting Safely">Read article in Campus News</a></p> 
        <p></p>  
        <div class="clear">
         &nbsp;
        </div> 
        <div class="tab_panel"> 
         <ul> 
          <li><a href="#tab1">About</a></li> 
          <li><a href="#tab2">Meetings/Minutes</a></li> 
          <li><a href="#tab3">Safety Tips</a></li> 
          <li><a href="#tab4">Contact</a></li> 
         </ul> 
         <div id="tab1"> 
          <h3>About</h3> 
          <p>     </p>
          <p>The EHS Committee consists of management and employee representatives who have an interest in the general promotion of safety and health at Green River Community College.&nbsp; The committee serves as an advisory group to the administration and is responsible for making recommendations on how to improve safety and health in the work place.&nbsp; The committee has been charged with the responsibility to define problems and remove obstacles to accident prevention; identify hazards and recommend corrective actions; help identify employee safety training needs; and establish accident investigation procedures for the College.<br><br>The committee meets the first Monday of each month from 2 - 3 p.m. in the AD Boardroom.&nbsp; For meetings that fall on the first day of a new quarter, the committee will meeting the following Monday.</p> 
          <p>The EHS is governed by Washington Administrative Code, which requires state workplaces to establish a committee of appointed and elected representatives to communicate and evaluate safety and health issues brought up in the workplace.</p>  
          <p></p> 
         </div> 
         <div id="tab2"> 
          <h3>Meetings/Minutes</h3> 
          <p>     </p>
          <p>The committee meets the first Monday of each month from 2 - 3 p.m. in the AD Boardroom.&nbsp; For meetings that fall on the first day of a new quarter, the committee will meet the following Monday.<br><br>Green River employees may find EHS meeting minutes and agendas may be found in the Enviormental Health and Safety Committee folder on the N drive.</p> 
          <ul> 
           <li>N:\Committees\Environmental Health and Safety Committee\Agenda |&nbsp;<a href="N:\Committees\Environmental Health and Safety Committee\Agenda" title="EHS agendas" target="_blank">Link - Internet Explorer only</a></li> 
           <li>N:\Committees\Environmental Health and Safety Committee\Minutes | <a href="N:\Committees\Environmental Health and Safety Committee\Minutes" title="Minutes" target="_blank">Link - Internet Explorer only</a></li> 
          </ul> 
          <p>If you are not an employee of Green River Community College and would like to review the agenda or minutes from our EHS committee please fill out our&nbsp;<a href="http://grcc.greenriver.edu/publicrecords/records-request.aspx" title="Public Request form">Public Records Request form</a>.&nbsp;</p>  
          <p></p> 
         </div> 
         <div id="tab3"> 
          <h3>Safety Tips</h3> 
          <p>     </p>
          <p>Green River cares. Check back periodically for news stories related to your safety.</p> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://www.greenriver.edu/about-us/campus-news/news/featured/2014-april-safety-tip.htm" title="Lifting Safety" target="_blank">Lifting Safety</a></li> 
           <li><a href="http://www.greenriver.edu/about-us/campus-news/news/featured/2014-march-safety-tip.htm" title="Slips, Trips and Falls" target="_blank">Slips, Trips and Falls</a></li> 
           <li><a href="http://www.greenriver.edu/about-us/news/campus-news/featured/2014-feb-safety-tip.htm" title="Preventing Back Pain" target="_blank">Preventing Back Pain</a></li> 
